      "span_text": "Anti-Fu1a antibody is thought to bind near the fusion peptide, since the mutation of amino acid 123, located seven amino acids from the aminoterminal end of F 1, eliminated the binding of this antibody to F protein without having an effect on the intracellular processing of the protein."
